https://leetcode.com/problems/binary-tree-right-side-view/description/

QUESTION:

Input: root = [1,2,3,null,5,null,4]
Output: [1,3,4]

SOLUTION:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Naive approach will be using queue 
TIME COMPLEXITY: O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY: O(n)
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    List<Integer>list=new ArrayList<>();
    public List<Integer> rightSideView(TreeNode root) {
        if(root==null)return list;
        Queue<TreeNode>q=new LinkedList<>();
        q.add(root);
        while(!q.isEmpty()){
            int size=q.size();
            for(int i=0;i<size;i++){
                TreeNode node=q.poll();
                if(i==0)list.add(node.val);
                if(node.right!=null)q.add(node.right);
                if(node.left!=null)q.add(node.left);
            }
        }
        return list;
    }
}

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Optimal approach:
TIME COMPLEXITY: O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY: O(log n) vs O(h)
do the dfs 
but everytime check the depth and array size() if equal then add to arraylist

/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    ArrayList<Integer>ar=new ArrayList<>();
    public List<Integer> rightSideView(TreeNode root) {
        rightside(root,0);
        return ar;
    }
    public void rightside(TreeNode root,int depth){
        if(root==null)return ;
        if(depth==ar.size())ar.add(root.val);
       rightside(root.right,depth+1);
       rightside(root.left,depth+1);
    }
}
